    "We also separate a portion of the DTR for clinician annotation for depression symptoms (Fig. 3).",
    "In the overall DSD framework, depicted in Fig. 1, we are ultimately interested in creating a robust DPD and a DSD model which are initially trained on human annotated samples, called \"DPD-Human\" model and \"DSD-Clinician\" model as depicted in Fig.",
    "The suffixes with these model names, such as \"Human,\" indicates that this model leverages the annotated samples from both non-clinicians and clinicians; \"Clinician\" indicates that this model leverages the samples for which the clinician's annotation is taken as more important (more explanation is 1 3",
    "Depression symptoms modelling from social media text: an LLM… provided later in Sect. 3.4).",
